text: Tasty Wonton mee. The Char Siew is nice, with good fat to lean meat ratio. Texture of the noodles is good.
I've been buying wonton noodles from this stall for over 10 years and still find it one of the most homely and satisfying bowl of noodles out of all the different stalls I've tried.

Paid $3.50 for a plate of wanton mee. The fried wanton and shrimp dumpling were sold out by 1.40pm. The noodles were springy. But the wantons and char siew were average. Service was fast but the lady taking orders forgot that I was eating the noodles at the coffee shop.
Good wanton noodles with choice of fried or normal wanton!

It is Okay only, typical wanton noodle. Nothing out of the blue or super yummy. If Long Q - No, not worth ur time to Q for it, or come all the way to try.

If u happy tp be in CCK and  just wld like to give it a try and no Q, sure.. no harm to try.
